It&#8217;s alleged the suspect, who is now in hospital under heavy police guard, overdosed on pills in an attempt to commit suicide. JOHANNESBURG Police say the suspect who held three people hostage with a knife in Randburg, is under police guard in hospital.It s alleged that the suspect who is a tenant at the property overdosed on pills in an attempt to commit suicide.He kept hostage the owner of the property, his wife and someone alleged to be his ex-girlfriend using two Swiss army knives on Wednesday.Police spokesperson Mavela Masondo says all hostages were released unharmed after police managed to negotiate with the perpetrator.Masondo says the man will be brought to book as soon as he is discharged from hospital. Yesterday we called the paramedics during the hostage drama, and after the victims were released the paramedics had to examine him. They discovered that he had taken an overdose of tablets and they said he needed to get medical treatment. He was taken to hospital. (Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)